removing this from entity Enseignant solve the problem.

    @JsonIdentityInfo(generator = ObjectIdGenerators.PropertyGenerator.class, property = &quot;id&quot;)


The `@JsonIdentityInfo` annotation with PropertyGenerator as the generator type and &quot;id&quot; as the property name tells Jackson to use object identity when serializing the class. In other words, when Jackson encounters the same object reference multiple times, it will only include the full serialization of that object once, and subsequent references to the same object will be represented as a reference to the original object&#39;s ID.

